bug.short_desc: Menus not being displayed in some applications
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: When using the X2Go Client from my Windows workstation some applications are not displaying any drop down menus when clicked. Using Fedora Spin LXDE.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): Name : x2goserver Arch : x86_64 Epoch : 0 Version : 4.0.1.19 Release : 11.fc25
Name : gtk3 Arch : x86_64 Epoch : 0 Version : 3.22.2 Release : 2.fc25
How reproducible: Consistently
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Start X2Go session, open PCManFM in session 2. Click a drop down menu 3. Menu title is selected but no menu drops down
Actual results: No drop down menu
Expected results: Menu should drop down and show menu options
Additional info: Possibly related to GTK3, see http://lists.x2go.org/pipermail/x2go-user/2016-November/004094.html.
Does x2goserver-4.0.1.20-1.fc25 make any difference? Do think it would, but it fixed some other stuff that I didn't expect it to.

Problem resolved with dnf updates. Unsure what resolved the problem but menu's now functioning normally in X2Go session (a pleasant side note is copy / paste now works also). Still at
Name : x2goserver Arch : x86_64 Epoch : 0 Version : 4.0.1.19 Release : 11.fc25
but gtk3 is now
Name : gtk3 Arch : x86_64 Epoch : 0 Version : 3.22.4 Release : 1.fc25
Okay, I'm going to assume that this was a gtk3 issue.
